text.section:
A surplus lines broker may not place surplus lines insurance with an unauthorized insurer that:
has not been approved by the Commissioner as a surplus lines insurer in accordance with § 3-318 of this subtitle;
for an insurer not domiciled in the State, has not qualified under § 3-303 of this subtitle;
has been determined by the Commissioner to be insolvent or unsafe financially under subsection (b) of this section; or
has been determined by the Commissioner to have refused to pay just claims.
